    "costs": "7500",
    "actions_taken": [
      "All operations shut down",
      "Affected areas barricaded off",
      "Safety stand down performed with all crews",
      "Basket retrieved safely",
      "All tools inspected and found in good working order",
      "P-tank swapped out instead of being repaired",
      "Damaged sections of handrails repaired",
      "All slings and lifting gear inspected and degraded slings taken out of service",
      "Replacement frequency of slings being revised by Enterprise"
    ],
    "summary": "On March 13, 2024, at approximately 20:10 hours, a 4x40' basket of plug and abandon tools weighing 13,000 pounds was being offloaded from the M/V GOL Cowboy to the upper cantilever of the jack-up Enterprise 264 using the port side crane. The stinger, rated for 9.80 tons in vertical pull, failed due to internal corrosion buildup from moisture in the socket. The basket fell and landed on the control room, P-tanks, and platform on top of the living quarters, causing structural damage estimated at $7,500. No injuries occurred. The failure to inspect the stinger prior to use was identified as a significant contributing factor.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Preventive Maintenance Daily checklist should clearly identify inspecting the stinger as a required step",
      "Cold work permits and Job Safety Analysis documents should specify inspecting the stinger",
      "Revision of sling and lifting gear replacement frequency"
    ],
